---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import SiteIcon from '../components/SiteIcon.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/urls';
---

<BaseLayout title="Our Story" description="Discover Temple Aviv Judea's journey from a 1970s Bible study to a vibrant Messianic Jewish congregation with a permanent home in Fullerton.">
  <PageHero eyebrow="From the wilderness to the promised land" title="A story of faithfulness." intro="What began around a table in a living room grew into one of the early modern Messianic Jewish congregations. It became a lasting home for Jewish and Gentile believers." accent="gold" />

  <section class="mosaic-feature mosaic-gold" aria-label="Temple artwork">
    <div class="shell mosaic-frame" data-reveal="wipe"><img src={withBase('/images/temple-mosaic.webp')} alt="Mosaic artwork of Jerusalem, the Temple, and worshippers at the Western Wall" width="853" height="364" /></div>
  </section>

  <section class="section story-intro">
    <div class="shell narrow prose-large" data-reveal>
      <span class="drop-mark"><SiteIcon name="jewish-star" size={27} /></span>
      <p>In 1974 in Fullerton, a Jewish believer separately shared the Good News with Mike Davis and Corey Sylvester, then introduced them after each believed. Mike’s parents and his 83-year-old grandmother soon believed as well. A non-Jewish family living two doors from them on Flatbush Avenue in Norwalk lovingly discipled the family through informal Friday-night Bible studies. The study opened to others and grew.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="timeline-section">
    <div class="shell timeline" data-stagger>
      <article class="timeline-entry">
        <div class="timeline-year">1978</div>
        <div class="timeline-content"><span class="eyebrow">A congregation is born</span><h2>Jewish faith made whole in Yeshua.</h2><p>On February 24, the open Bible study formally became Temple Aviv Judea, one of the early Messianic Jewish congregations in the United States and the world. Mike Davis became its founding Messianic Rabbi, and Corey Sylvester became its cantor. Their first aim was to obtain a kosher Torah and an ark; the congregation was blessed with two Torah scrolls.</p></div>
      </article>
      <article class="timeline-entry">
        <div class="timeline-year">1978 to 2013</div>
        <div class="timeline-content"><span class="eyebrow">A family on the move</span><h2>Many addresses. One calling.</h2><p>During its first 35 years, the congregation moved from Norwalk to La Mirada, La Palma, Orange, Yorba Linda, and then back to Orange. In 1979, Corey and Hilary were married at TAJ. Through every move, the community continued to celebrate weddings, b’nei mitzvah, funerals, feasts, and weekly Shabbat together.</p></div>
      </article>
      <article class="timeline-entry">
        <div class="timeline-year">2004</div>
        <div class="timeline-content"><span class="eyebrow">Passing the mantle</span><h2>A legacy carried forward.</h2><p>After Rabbi Mike Davis went home to the L-rd in August 2004, Corey Sylvester was licensed and ordained as Messianic Rabbi. The mission continued: reach the lost sheep of Israel, open the doors to Jewish people and the Nations, and embody a community where dividing walls are broken down.</p></div>
      </article>
      <article class="timeline-entry featured-entry">
        <div class="timeline-year">2014</div>
        <div class="timeline-content"><span class="eyebrow">The first miracle</span><h2>At last, a home in Fullerton.</h2><p>On October 1, after 36 years of moving from place to place, TAJ purchased and moved into a permanent home on busy Commonwealth Avenue near downtown Fullerton. Even obtaining the loan was considered a miracle: the congregation, including its rabbi, was entirely volunteer-led and paid no salaries. It began this chapter with a $1.2 million outstanding loan and a visible home for its mission of love—building a bridge between the Jewish people and the Nations.</p><picture class="story-building"><source media="(max-width: 760px)" srcset={withBase('/images/building-mobile.webp')} /><img src={withBase('/images/live/worship-dance.webp')} alt="Temple Aviv Judea’s building at 704 East Commonwealth Avenue in Fullerton" width="1280" height="720" loading="lazy" /></picture></div>
      </article>
      <article class="timeline-entry">
        <div class="timeline-year">2020</div>
        <div class="timeline-content"><span class="eyebrow">The second miracle</span><h2>Paid in full.</h2><p>After standing in faith for six years, the congregation paid off the building loan in August, during the pandemic. TAJ remembers this milestone as a testimony to G-d’s provision and the faithfulness of the community that sustained its lasting home.</p></div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section rabbi-section">
    <div class="shell rabbi-grid" data-stagger>
      <img src={withBase('/images/live/rabbi-corey.webp')} alt="Rabbi Corey Sylvester teaching outdoors with a book and headset microphone" width="1254" height="1254" loading="lazy" />
      <div><span class="eyebrow">Meet Rabbi Corey Sylvester</span><h2>Clarity, kindness, and joyful faith.</h2><p class="lead">Rabbi Corey is known for teaching with clarity, offering grounded spiritual guidance, and bringing warmth and humor to community life.</p><p>Together with his wife, Hilary, he has served Temple Aviv Judea with a deep love for the L-RD and for the congregation’s mishpachah.</p><a class="arrow-link" href="mailto:info@avivjudea.org?subject=Connect%20with%20Rabbi%20Corey">Connect with Rabbi Corey <SiteIcon name="arrow-right" size={19} /></a></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="vision-section">
    <div class="shell vision-inner" data-reveal>
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-light">The story still unfolds</span>
      <h2>A light to the community and to the world.</h2>
      <p>TAJ’s vision is a thriving Messianic Jewish community center: a place for Torah learning, dialogue about Yeshua, Shabbat dinners, creative arts, and open doors.</p>
      <a class="button button-gold" href={withBase('/visit/')}>Become part of the story</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
